---
import Page from '../../layouts/Page.astro';
import SectionBanner from '../../components/ui/SectionBanner.astro';
---

<Page
  title="3ds Max Tools & Scripting"
  description="MAXScript and Python tools for batch processing, scene cleanup, render management. 3ds Max since version 1. Vision Graphics Kft., Budapest."
>

  <SectionBanner
    image="/_img/banners/banner-3dsmax.jpg"
    label="Make 3ds Max Work For You"
    title="3ds Max Tools & Scripting"
    size="page"
    headingLevel="h1"
  />
  <div class="service-page">

    <div class="service-breadcrumb">
      <a href="/services/">Services</a>
      <span>→</span>
      <span>3ds Max Tools & Scripting</span>
    </div>

    <p class="section-label">Service</p>
    <h2 class="display-lg service-h1">3ds Max Tools &amp; Scripting</h2>
    <p class="service-tagline-large">Custom tools for MAX users who've hit the ceiling.</p>

    <div class="service-body-grid">
      <div class="service-main">

        <p class="service-lead">
          After 30 years of wrestling with 3ds Max — yes, since version 1 — we know exactly
          what breaks and how to fix it. More importantly, we know how to stop those problems
          from coming back. MAXScript and Python tools built for your specific production
          problems, not generic plugins that almost do what you need.
        </p>

        <h2 class="service-section-h2">What's slowing you down?</h2>
        <p class="body-text">
          Ever notice how much time you spend fixing the same issues over and over?
          Old files that won't open, materials that look wrong, scenes that crash just when
          you need them most. We fix that — not just for one file, but for all of them.
        </p>

      </div>

      <aside class="service-sidebar">
        <div class="sidebar-block">
          <h3 class="sidebar-label">Experience</h3>
          <ul class="sidebar-list">
            <li>3ds Max since version 1</li>
            <li>MAXScript: 25+ years</li>
            <li>Python: 10+ years</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="sidebar-block">
          <h3 class="sidebar-label">Pricing</h3>
          <p class="sidebar-price">By scope</p>
          <p class="sidebar-note">Simple scripts from €500. Complex automation tools quoted on scope. Maintenance retainers available.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="sidebar-cta">
          <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-primary sidebar-btn">Discuss Your Needs</a>
          <a href="/services/workflow-optimization/" class="btn btn-ghost">Workflow optimization</a>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>

  </div>

  <SectionBanner
    image="/_img/banners/banner-general.jpg"
    label="MAX Headaches"
    title="We Handle What Breaks"
    headingLevel="h2"
  />
  <div class="service-section container">
    <p class="section-body">
      We specialize in complex, large-scale 3ds Max files that exhaust RAM or crash on other
      machines. Because we use these tools ourselves in production, they get maintained when
      3ds Max updates break things.
    </p>
    <ul class="results-list">
      <li>Trace and fix mysterious crashes that waste your time</li>
      <li>Clean up messy geometry causing render problems</li>
      <li>Sort out material libraries that no longer make sense</li>
      <li>Remove corrupt objects that slow everything down</li>
      <li>Make old files work with your current MAX version</li>
      <li>Recover scenes that crash on delivery deadline</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <SectionBanner
    image="/_img/banners/banner-tech.jpg"
    label="Custom Scripts"
    title="Automate the Repetitive"
    headingLevel="h2"
  />
  <div class="service-section container">
    <p class="section-body">
      Why do the same task 100 times when you could do it once? We build MAXScripts and
      Python tools that automate your repetitive work — built for how you actually work,
      not for generic use.
    </p>
    <div class="deliverable-grid">
      {[
        {
          title: 'Batch Processing',
          desc: 'Process hundreds of files without clicking a thing. Render submission, camera switching, output naming, V-Ray preset switching — automated.',
        },
        {
          title: 'Scene Cleanup',
          desc: 'Fix common geometry issues automatically. Remove duplicates, fix missing materials, purge unused assets, standardize naming conventions across a folder of files.',
        },
        {
          title: 'Asset Management',
          desc: 'Track, relink, and consolidate external assets across complex scenes. Prevent the "missing texture" problem in production. Batch replace and export materials.',
        },
        {
          title: 'Custom UI Panels',
          desc: 'Rollout panels and toolbars that put your most-used operations one click away. Built for how you actually work.',
        },
        {
          title: 'Material Processing',
          desc: 'Batch replace, update, or export materials. Useful when working with large BIM imports or standardizing across a project series.',
        },
        {
          title: 'Python Integration',
          desc: 'Connect 3ds Max to external systems via Python — file servers, databases, project management tools, and AI services.',
        },
      ].map(d => (
        <div class="deliverable-card">
          <h3 class="deliverable-title">{d.title}</h3>
          <p class="deliverable-desc">{d.desc}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>

  <SectionBanner
    image="/_img/banners/banner-workflow.jpg"
    label="How We Work"
    title="Listen. Analyse. Solve."
    headingLevel="h2"
  />
  <div class="service-section container">
    <div class="process-grid">
      {[
        {
          step: '01',
          title: 'First, We Listen',
          desc: 'We start by understanding your workflow. What takes too long? What breaks most often? Where do you waste time? No guessing — we learn your specific situation.',
        },
        {
          step: '02',
          title: 'Then, We Analyse',
          desc: 'We dig into your files, find the real problems (not just the symptoms), and figure out what\'s causing them. We know the difference between a symptom and a root cause.',
        },
        {
          step: '03',
          title: 'Finally, We Solve',
          desc: 'We build solutions that fix your current problems and stop them from coming back — working with your team\'s skills and fitting your actual workflow. Either teach you or handle it for you.',
        },
      ].map(p => (
        <div class="process-card">
          <span class="process-step">{p.step}</span>
          <h3 class="process-title">{p.title}</h3>
          <p class="process-desc">{p.desc}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>

</Page>

<style>
  .service-page {
    max-width: 1060px;
    padding-top: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
  }

  .service-breadcrumb {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: var(--fs-xs);
    color: var(--color-text-faint); margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .service-breadcrumb a { color: var(--color-text-muted); text-decoration: none; transition: color 200ms; }
  .service-breadcrumb a:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }

  .service-h1 { margin: 0.5rem 0 0.75rem; }
  .service-tagline-large { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: var(--fs-h6); font-style: italic; color: var(--color-accent); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .service-lead { font-size: var(--fs-small); color: var(--color-text-muted); max-width: 65ch; line-height: 1.75; margin: 0 0 1.5rem; }

  .service-body-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 240px; gap: 4rem; align-items: start; }
  .service-main { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; }

  .service-section-h2 { font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: var(--fs-xs); font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-text-faint); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }

  .body-text { font-size: var(--fs-small); color: var(--color-text-muted); max-width: 65ch; line-height: 1.75; margin: 0; }

  /* Sub-sections */
  .service-section { padding-block: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem); }

  .section-body { font-size: var(--fs-small); color: var(--color-text-muted); max-width: 65ch; line-height: 1.75; margin: 0 0 1.5rem; }

  .results-list { list-style: none; padding: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.6rem; }
  .results-list li { font-size: var(--fs-small); color: var(--color-text-muted); padding-left: 1.25rem; position: relative; line-height: 1.5; }
  .results-list li::before { content: '→'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--color-accent); font-size: var(--fs-xs); }

  .deliverable-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1px; background: var(--color-border); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .deliverable-card { background: var(--color-surface); padding: 1.5rem; transition: background 200ms; }
  .deliverable-card:hover { background: var(--color-surface-2); }
  .deliverable-title { font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: var(--fs-small); font-weight: 500; color: var(--color-text); margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }
  .deliverable-desc { font-size: var(--fs-xs); color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0; max-width: none; }

  .process-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 1px; background: var(--color-border); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .process-card { background: var(--color-surface); padding: 1.5rem; transition: background 200ms; }
  .process-card:hover { background: var(--color-surface-2); }
  .process-step { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--fs-xs); color: var(--color-accent); display: block; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .process-title { font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: var(--fs-small); font-weight: 500; color: var(--color-text); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .process-desc { font-size: var(--fs-xs); color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0; }

  /* Sidebar */
  .service-sidebar { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2rem; position: sticky; top: 5rem; }
  .sidebar-block { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.6rem; }
  .sidebar-label { font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: var(--fs-xs); font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-text-faint); }
  .sidebar-list { list-style: none; padding: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.35rem; }
  .sidebar-list li { font-size: var(--fs-xs); color: var(--color-text-muted); padding-left: 0.9rem; position: relative; }
  .sidebar-list li::before { content: '—'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--color-border); font-size: var(--fs-xs); }
  .sidebar-price { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: var(--fs-h5); font-weight: 300; color: var(--color-text); margin: 0; }
  .sidebar-note { font-size: var(--fs-xs); color: var(--color-text-faint); line-height: 1.5; margin: 0; max-width: none; }
  .sidebar-cta { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; }
  .sidebar-btn { width: 100%; justify-content: center; }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .service-body-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .service-sidebar { position: static; }
    .deliverable-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .process-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
